()🔹 AccessReviewDecision kya hai?
👉 AccessReviewDecision = reviewer ka final decision object
Simple words me:-
Ye object store karta hai ki reviewer ne kya decision liya + uska reason + metadata.

🔥 Ye kyun alag object hai?
Tu soch raha hoga:-
👉 "decision toh AccessReviewItem me hi hai, phir ye alag kyun?"

✔️ Reason:-
AccessReviewItem = current state
AccessReviewDecision = history / record / audit log.

🧠 Simple Example:-
AccessReviewItem (Admin Role):-
Reviewer 1 → APPROVE
Reviewer 2 → REVOKE
Manager → APPROVE
👉 Ye sab decisions ek hi jagah store nahi hote.
👉 Har ek decision ka record banega:-
AccessReviewDecision 1 (Reviewer 1)
AccessReviewDecision 2 (Reviewer 2)
AccessReviewDecision 3 (Manager)

🔥 AccessReviewDecision ke andar kya hota hai?
Typical fields 👇

1️⃣ decision:-
👉 kya action liya
APPROVE
REVOKE
ABSTAIN

2️⃣ reviewer:-
👉 kisne decision liya
Reviewer: manager123

3️⃣ comments:-
👉 reason kya diya
"Access required for project"

4️⃣ date / timestamp:-
👉 kab decision liya
2026-03-26 10:30 AM

5️⃣ completed / status:-
👉 decision complete hai ya nahi.

🔥 Ye kya karta hai?
👉 Main kaam:-
✔️ 1. Audit trail maintain karta hai
Kisne kya decision liya → track hota hai
✔️ 2. Multi-level approval support
Manager → Owner → Security team
✔️ 3. Compliance ke liye proof
Audit me poocha jaata hai:-
"kisne approve kiya?"

🔥 Kya ye DB me store hota hai?
👉 ✅ YES — 100% store hota hai database me
🗄️ Database level pe
AccessReviewItem table/object
AccessReviewDecision alag entity/table.
--------------------------------------------
🔹 1️⃣ getDecision():-
👉 Description:-
Reviewer ka final decision return karta hai.
AccessReviewDecision d = new AccessReviewDecision();
d.setDecision("APPROVE");
System.out.println(d.getDecision());
✔️ Output:-
APPROVE

🔹 2️⃣ getDecisionOk():-
👉 Description:-
Safe getter (null handle karta hai)
AccessReviewDecision d = new AccessReviewDecision();
System.out.println(d.getDecisionOk());
✔️ Output:-
null
👉 Agar set kare:-
d.setDecision("REVOKE");
System.out.println(d.getDecisionOk());
✔️ Output:-
REVOKE

🔹 3️⃣ setDecision(String decision):-
👉 Description:-
Decision set karta hai
d.setDecision("APPROVE");
✔️ Output:-
(no direct output)

🔹 4️⃣ hasDecision():-
👉 Description:-
Check karta hai decision diya gaya hai ya nahi
AccessReviewDecision d = new AccessReviewDecision();
System.out.println(d.hasDecision());
✔️ Output:-
false
👉 After set:-
d.setDecision("APPROVE");
System.out.println(d.hasDecision());
✔️ Output:-
true

🔹 5️⃣ getComments():-
👉 Description:-
Reviewer ka comment return karta hai
d.setComments("Access needed");
System.out.println(d.getComments());
✔️ Output:-
Access needed

🔹 6️⃣ getCommentsOk():-
👉 Description:
Safe getter (null handle)
AccessReviewDecision d = new AccessReviewDecision();
System.out.println(d.getCommentsOk());
✔️ Output:-
null

🔹 7️⃣ setComments(String comments):-
👉 Description:-
Comment set karta hai
d.setComments("Approved for project");
✔️ Output:-
(no output)

🔹 8️⃣ hasComments():-
👉 Description:-
Check karta hai comment hai ya nahi
System.out.println(d.hasComments());
✔️ Output:-
true / false

🔹 9️⃣ setCommentsNil();-
👉 Description:-
Intentionally null set karta hai
d.setCommentsNil();
System.out.println(d.getCommentsOk());
✔️ Output:-
null

🔹 🔟 unsetComments():-
👉 Description:-
Field completely remove kar deta hai
d.unsetComments();
System.out.println(d.hasComments());

✔️ Output:-
false

